You don’t realize how much you miss normalcy until you are reunited with it. And then you finally feel free!  Yes, I’ve tried to make the best of 2020, participating in as many activities as COVID restrictions would allow. I’ve pushed the envelope with mandates but even so things didn’t feel normal. Then you drive through KS on your way to OK for - gasp! - Thanksgiving dinner with family. At gas stations, most aren’t wearing masks & no one glares at your bare face. When you get to your hotel, they welcome you with a care package & news that hot breakfast is served until 10am & the gym & pool are open until midnight (no mask needed!) At the restaurant, tables are spaced normally. Waitresses smile. Stores have regular hours. People interact without hesitation or fear. You feel human again. You didn’t realize how much you missed this feeling, how truly weird things have gotten back in CO. It makes you wonder, for the umpteenth time this year, where you truly want to call home...
